The United for Kiambu team says it will upgrade Chania Bridge in Thika town to reduce traffic jams.The team is made up of five leaders who want to take over the Kiambu county leadership from Governor William Kabogo.They include Kabete MP Ferdinand Waititu, who won the JP primaries to run for governor.Others are Waititu&rsquo;s running mate James Nyoro, Rev David Kariuki, popularly known as Gakuyo, trader John Mugwe, lawyer Aquiline Njoki and Thika Town MP Alice Ng&rsquo;ang&rsquo;aOn Monday when they inspected the bridge, Waititu said they will use their personal funds to upgrade it.Work will begin this week,they said.In June 2015, Kabogo said the county would upgrade the bridge and make it a dual carriageway. It connects Thika town to Murang&rsquo;a county.No construction has been done.